Menander (ᾗ 28).——Cneius Publicius Menander, a freedman, and formerly a Greek prisoner of war. A senatorial commission took him as an interpreter to Greeee, and to his native city. By returning to his native city his former citizenship would revive, and ipso facto he would lose his Roman citizenship. The Roman people passed a special law to enable him, if he returned to Rome, to retain his Roman citizenship.
